\frac{3-x}{(x^2+3)(x+3)}=\frac{Ax+B}{x^2+3}+\frac C{x+3} 
= \frac{-\frac12\cdot x+\frac 12}{x^2+3}+\frac {\frac 12}{x+3}=\dfrac 12\left(\frac{1-x}{x^2 + 3}\right) + \dfrac 12\left(\frac 1{x+3}\right)
\frac{3-x}{(x^2+3)(x+3)}=\frac{Ax+B}{x^2+3}+\frac{C}{x+3}
\frac{Ax+B}{x^2+3}+\frac{C}{x+3}=\frac{(Ax+B)(x+3)+C(x^2+3)}{(x^2+3)(x+3)}=\frac{(A+C)x^2+(3A+B)x+3(B+C)}{(x^2+3)(x+3)}
x^2:A+C=0,\quad x:(3A+B)=-1,\quad\text{constant}: 3(B+C)=3
